---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
import { Image } from 'astro:assets';
import { getCollection } from 'astro:content';
import heroImg from '../../assets/services/ai-strategy-hero.webp';
import caseImg from '../../assets/services/ai-strategy-case-study.webp';

const relatedTags = ['ai', 'ai & marketing'];
const allPosts = await getCollection('blog');
const relatedPosts = allPosts
  .filter(post => relatedTags.includes(post.data.tag.toLowerCase()))
  .sort((a, b) => b.data.date.valueOf() - a.data.date.valueOf())
  .slice(0, 3);
---
<Base title="AI & Hybrid Marketing Strategy for B2B | The B2B Tinkerers" description="AI won't replace your marketing team. But teams that use AI well will outcompete those that don't. We help B2B companies build the hybrid model that actually works.">

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="sv-hero">
  <div class="sv-hero-bg">
    <Image src={heroImg} alt="Circuit board pattern merging with organic leaf veins" format="webp" quality={85} loading="eager" fetchpriority="high" style="width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;display:block;" />
  </div>
  <div class="sv-hero-overlay"></div>
  <div class="sv-hero-content">
    <div class="sv-eyebrow">Service 05</div>
    <h1 class="sv-h1">AI & Hybrid<br/>Marketing Strategy</h1>
    <p class="sv-subtitle">AI won't replace your marketing team. But teams that use AI well will outcompete those that don't. We help B2B companies understand where AI genuinely adds value in their marketing operation and build the workflows to make it stick.</p>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- THE PROBLEM -->
<section class="sv-problem">
  <div class="sv-problem-inner">
    <div class="sv-problem-left">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">The challenge</div>
      <h2 class="sv-h2">Everyone is talking about AI.<br/>Almost nobody is using it well.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="sv-problem-right">
      <p>There is enormous pressure to "do something with AI" right now. Leadership reads the headlines, sees competitors announcing AI initiatives, and wants to know the plan. But the honest truth is that most B2B marketing teams have no clarity on what AI should actually do for them. The urgency is real. The direction is missing.</p>
      <p>So teams experiment. Someone starts using ChatGPT for blog drafts. Another person tries an AI tool for ad copy. A third explores automated reporting. None of it connects to a strategy. None of it scales. And when leadership asks what the ROI is, nobody has a good answer. The tools are powerful, but isolated experiments don't compound into anything meaningful.</p>
      <p>Worse, some teams rush to automate processes that were broken to begin with. AI doesn't fix a bad content strategy. It just produces bad content faster. The real question is not "where can we use AI?" It is "where does human judgment matter most, and where does it not?" Get that wrong and you waste budget. Get it right and you build a genuine competitive advantage.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- WHAT WE DELIVER -->
<section class="sv-deliver">
  <div class="sv-deliver-inner">
    <div class="sv-deliver-header">
      <div class="section-eyebrow">What we deliver</div>
      <h2 class="sv-h2">A practical AI strategy, not a science experiment.</h2>
      <p class="sv-deliver-intro">We build AI strategies that create value, not hype. Every recommendation is grounded in your team's actual capabilities, your real workflows, and what will genuinely move the needle for your marketing operation.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="sv-deliver-grid">
      <div class="sv-deliver-card">
        <div class="sv-deliver-head">
          <svg class="sv-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><rect x="4" y="4" width="16" height="16" rx="2"/><path d="M9 9h.01"/><path d="M15 9h.01"/><path d="M9 15h.01"/><path d="M15 15h.01"/><path d="M9 12h6"/><path d="M12 9v6"/></svg>
          <div class="sv-deliver-label">AI readiness assessment</div>
        </div>
        <div class="sv-deliver-desc">Where your team, data, and processes are today. What's ready for AI and what isn't. A clear-eyed evaluation before anyone starts buying tools or building workflows.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sv-deliver-card">
        <div class="sv-deliver-head">
          <svg class="sv-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="23 4 23 10 17 10"/><polyline points="1 20 1 14 7 14"/><path d="M3.51 9a9 9 0 0 1 14.85-3.36L23 10M1 14l4.64 4.36A9 9 0 0 0 20.49 15"/></svg>
          <div class="sv-deliver-label">Content and campaign automation strategy</div>
        </div>
        <div class="sv-deliver-desc">Which workflows benefit from automation. Which need human judgment. Where the handoffs live. A practical map of what to automate, what to augment, and what to leave alone.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sv-deliver-card">
        <div class="sv-deliver-head">
          <svg class="sv-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><path d="M12 2l-2 7H3l5.5 4.5L6 21l6-4.5L18 21l-2.5-7.5L21 9h-7z"/><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="3"/><path d="M5 5l1.5 1.5"/><path d="M17.5 17.5L19 19"/><path d="M19 5l-1.5 1.5"/><path d="M5.5 17.5L4 19"/></svg>
          <div class="sv-deliver-label">Tool selection and stack integration</div>
        </div>
        <div class="sv-deliver-desc">The right tools for your actual needs. Not the trendiest, not the cheapest. The ones that fit your workflows, integrate with your existing stack, and your team will actually use.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="sv-deliver-card">
        <div class="sv-deliver-head">
          <svg class="sv-icon" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"><polyline points="22 12 18 12 15 21 9 3 6 12 2 12"/><path d="M18 6l2-2 2 2"/><path d="M20 4v6"/></svg>
          <div class="sv-deliver-label">Team capability building</div>
        </div>
        <div class="sv-deliver-desc">Training your team to work with AI, not be replaced by it. Practical skills, not theory. The goal is confidence and competence, not dependence on external consultants.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- HOW WE WORK -->
<section class="sv-process">
  <div class="sv-process-inner">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">How we work</div>
    <h2 class="sv-h2">From assessment to operational AI in 6-8 weeks.</h2>
    <div class="sv-process-grid">
      <div class="sv-process-step">
        <span class="sv-process-num">01</span>
        <div class="sv-process-title">Assessment</div>
        <div class="sv-process-body">Current workflows, team capabilities, data landscape, tool audit. We understand where you are before recommending where to go.</div>
        <span class="sv-process-tag">Week 1-2</span>
      </div>
      <div class="sv-process-step">
        <span class="sv-process-num">02</span>
        <div class="sv-process-title">Strategy</div>
        <div class="sv-process-body">Use case prioritisation, build vs buy decisions, integration architecture. The hard choices about where AI fits and where it doesn't.</div>
        <span class="sv-process-tag">Week 3-4</span>
      </div>
      <div class="sv-process-step">
        <span class="sv-process-num">03</span>
        <div class="sv-process-title">Pilot</div>
        <div class="sv-process-body">Implement 2-3 high-impact workflows. Measure results. Iterate. Real proof of value before committing to a full rollout.</div>
        <span class="sv-process-tag">Week 5-6</span>
      </div>
      <div class="sv-process-step">
        <span class="sv-process-num">04</span>
        <div class="sv-process-title">Scale</div>
        <div class="sv-process-body">Team training, documentation, rollout plan for remaining use cases. Everything your team needs to run this without us.</div>
        <span class="sv-process-tag">Week 7-8</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- STATS -->
<section class="sv-stats">
  <div class="sv-stats-inner">
    <div class="section-eyebrow sv-stats-eyebrow">The numbers</div>
    <h2 class="sv-h2 sv-stats-title">The AI gap is already here.</h2>
    <div class="sv-stats-grid">
      <div class="sv-stat-card sv-stat-1">
        <span class="sv-stat-num">64%</span>
        <span class="sv-stat-label">of B2B marketers say AI will significantly impact their strategy but only 19% have a formal plan</span>
        <span class="sv-stat-source">Salesforce State of Marketing 2024</span>
      </div>
      <div class="sv-stat-card sv-stat-2">
        <span class="sv-stat-num">40%</span>
        <span class="sv-stat-label">productivity increase in marketing teams that have successfully integrated AI into core workflows</span>
        <span class="sv-stat-source">McKinsey 2024</span>
      </div>
      <div class="sv-stat-card sv-stat-3">
        <span class="sv-stat-num">5x</span>
        <span class="sv-stat-label">faster content production with AI-augmented workflows while maintaining quality standards</span>
        <span class="sv-stat-source">HubSpot 2024</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CASE STUDY -->
<section class="sv-case">
  <div class="sv-case-inner">
    <div class="section-eyebrow">Case in point</div>
    <div class="sv-case-grid">
      <div class="sv-case-text">
        <h2 class="sv-h2">A B2B SaaS company reduced content production time by 60% and increased output quality by integrating AI into their editorial workflow.</h2>
        <p>The marketing team was producing 4 pieces of content per month and struggling to keep up. Demand from sales for case studies, thought leadership, and product content was growing, but headcount was not. The team was stuck in a cycle of producing just enough to stay visible, without the bandwidth to focus on quality or strategy.</p>
        <p>We mapped their editorial workflow end to end, identified where AI could handle research, outlines, and first drafts, and built a human-AI pipeline with clear quality gates. Each piece still went through human editorial review, but the time spent on the low-value production work dropped dramatically.</p>
        <p>Within 8 weeks, output increased from 4 to 12 pieces per month. More importantly, the team spent more time on strategy, positioning, and distribution. Content quality improved because writers were editing and refining rather than staring at blank pages. The bottleneck shifted from "can we produce enough" to "what should we produce next."</p>
      </div>
      <div class="sv-case-img">
        <Image src={caseImg} alt="Human fingerprint pattern merging with digital circuit traces" format="webp" quality={85} loading="lazy" style="width:100%;height:100%;object-fit:cover;display:block;" />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- RELATED INSIGHTS -->
{relatedPosts.length > 0 && (
<section class="sv-insights">
  <div class="sv-insights-inner">
    <div class="sv-insights-header">
      <div>
        <div class="section-eyebrow">Related insights</div>
        <h2 class="sv-h2">What we're writing about AI and marketing.</h2>
      </div>
      <a class="sv-insights-all" href="/insights">All articles →</a>
    </div>
    <div class="sv-insights-grid">
      {relatedPosts.map(post => (
        <a class="sv-insight-card" href={`/insights/${post.slug}`}>
          <span class="sv-insight-tag">{post.data.tag}</span>
          <div class="sv-insight-title">{post.data.title}</div>
          <div class="sv-insight-meta">
            <span class="sv-insight-date">{post.data.date.toLocaleDateString('en-GB',{month:'short',year:'numeric'})}</span>
            <span class="sv-insight-arrow">Read more →</span>
          </div>
        </a>
      ))}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
)}

<!-- CTA -->
<section class="sv-cta">
  <div class="sv-cta-inner">
    <h2 class="sv-cta-h2">Ready to make AI work for your marketing team?</h2>
    <p class="sv-cta-sub">30 minutes. No pitch. Just an honest conversation about where AI can actually help your operation.</p>
    <a class="btn-primary" href="#contact">Let's talk →</a>
  </div>
</section>

</Base>

<style>
/* HERO */
.sv-hero{position:relative;min-height:50vh;padding:calc(68px + clamp(48px,7vw,80px)) var(--pad) clamp(48px,6vw,72px);display:flex;align-items:flex-end;overflow:hidden}
.sv-hero-bg{position:absolute;inset:0;z-index:0}
.sv-hero-overlay{position:absolute;inset:0;z-index:1;background:linear-gradient(120deg,rgba(7,35,26,.94) 0%,rgba(13,51,36,.82) 45%,rgba(31,115,81,.42) 100%)}
.sv-hero-content{position:relative;z-index:2;max-width:620px}
.sv-eyebrow{font-size:13px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:.01em;color:var(--chartreuse);display:inline-block;margin-bottom:18px}
.sv-eyebrow::before{display:none}
.sv-h1{font-family:'Bricolage Grotesque Variable',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(30px,5vw,64px);font-weight:800;letter-spacing:-0.04em;line-height:.97;color:var(--cream);margin-bottom:24px}
.sv-subtitle{font-size:clamp(14px,1.8vw,17px);line-height:1.85;color:rgba(245,240,232,0.62);max-width:600px}
@media(max-width:820px){
  .sv-hero{min-height:auto;padding-top:calc(68px + 44px)}
  .sv-hero-overlay{background:linear-gradient(180deg,rgba(7,35,26,.92) 0%,rgba(13,51,36,.9) 100%)}
}

/* PROBLEM */
.sv-problem{padding:clamp(72px,9vw,112px) var(--pad);background:var(--cream)}
.sv-problem-inner{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1.6fr;gap:clamp(36px,6vw,88px);align-items:start}
@media(max-width:760px){.sv-problem-inner{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
.sv-h2{font-family:'Bricolage Grotesque Variable',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(22px,3vw,38px);font-weight:800;letter-spacing:-0.04em;line-height:1.05;color:var(--forest);margin-bottom:16px}
.sv-problem-right p{font-size:clamp(14px,1.6vw,16px);line-height:1.9;color:rgba(26,26,26,.65);margin-bottom:22px}
.sv-problem-right p:last-child{margin-bottom:0}

/* DELIVER */
.sv-deliver{padding:clamp(72px,9vw,112px) var(--pad);background:var(--linen)}
.sv-deliver-inner{max-width:1100px}
.sv-deliver-header{max-width:640px;margin-bottom:clamp(36px,5vw,56px)}
.sv-deliver-intro{font-size:clamp(13px,1.5vw,15px);line-height:1.85;color:var(--gray)}
.sv-deliver-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:2px}
@media(max-width:520px){.sv-deliver-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
.sv-deliver-card{background:var(--cream);padding:clamp(24px,3vw,36px) clamp(20px,2.5vw,28px);transition:background .2s}
.sv-deliver-card:hover{background:var(--forest)}
.sv-deliver-head{display:flex;align-items:center;gap:12px;margin-bottom:12px}
.sv-icon{width:22px;height:22px;color:var(--forest);flex-shrink:0;transition:color .2s}
.sv-deliver-card:hover .sv-icon{color:var(--lime)}
.sv-deliver-label{font-family:'Bricolage Grotesque Variable',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(14px,1.8vw,17px);font-weight:700;color:var(--forest);line-height:1.25;transition:color .2s}
.sv-deliver-card:hover .sv-deliver-label{color:var(--cream)}
.sv-deliver-desc{font-size:12.5px;line-height:1.7;color:rgba(26,26,26,.6);transition:color .2s}
.sv-deliver-card:hover .sv-deliver-desc{color:rgba(245,240,232,.58)}

/* PROCESS */
.sv-process{padding:clamp(72px,9vw,112px) var(--pad);background:var(--cream)}
.sv-process-inner{max-width:1100px}
.sv-process-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(4,1fr);gap:2px}
@media(max-width:900px){.sv-process-grid{grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr)}}
@media(max-width:480px){.sv-process-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
.sv-process-step{background:var(--linen);padding:clamp(20px,3vw,32px) clamp(16px,2.5vw,24px);transition:background .2s}
.sv-process-step:hover{background:var(--forest)}
.sv-process-num{font-family:'Bricolage Grotesque Variable',sans-serif;font-size:40px;font-weight:800;color:var(--forest);opacity:.2;display:block;line-height:1;margin-bottom:4px;transition:color .2s,opacity .2s}
.sv-process-step:hover .sv-process-num{color:var(--cream);opacity:.09}
.sv-process-title{font-family:'Bricolage Grotesque Variable',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(14px,1.8vw,17px);font-weight:700;color:var(--forest);margin-bottom:10px;transition:color .2s}
.sv-process-step:hover .sv-process-title{color:var(--cream)}
.sv-process-body{font-size:12px;line-height:1.7;color:rgba(26,26,26,.55);transition:color .2s}
.sv-process-step:hover .sv-process-body{color:rgba(245,240,232,.55)}
.sv-process-tag{display:inline-block;margin-top:14px;background:var(--chartreuse);color:var(--ink);font-size:10px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.04em;padding:5px 11px;border-radius:4px}

/* STATS */
.sv-stats{padding:clamp(72px,9vw,112px) var(--pad);background:var(--forest)}
.sv-stats-inner{max-width:1100px}
.sv-stats-eyebrow{color:var(--cream);opacity:.22;margin-bottom:16px}
.sv-stats-title{color:var(--cream);margin-bottom:36px}
.sv-stats-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:2px}
@media(max-width:700px){.sv-stats-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
.sv-stat-card{padding:clamp(24px,3vw,36px) clamp(20px,2.5vw,28px)}
.sv-stat-1,.sv-stat-3{background:var(--lime)}
.sv-stat-2{background:var(--mid)}
.sv-stat-num{font-family:'Bricolage Grotesque Variable',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(36px,5vw,56px);font-weight:800;line-height:1;display:block;margin-bottom:10px}
.sv-stat-1 .sv-stat-num,.sv-stat-3 .sv-stat-num{color:var(--forest)}
.sv-stat-2 .sv-stat-num{color:var(--lime)}
.sv-stat-label{font-size:12px;line-height:1.6;display:block}
.sv-stat-1 .sv-stat-label,.sv-stat-3 .sv-stat-label{color:var(--forest)}
.sv-stat-2 .sv-stat-label{color:rgba(245,240,232,.92)}
.sv-stat-source{display:block;margin-top:14px;font-size:9px;font-weight:700;letter-spacing:.08em;text-transform:uppercase}
.sv-stat-1 .sv-stat-source,.sv-stat-3 .sv-stat-source{color:rgba(28,74,58,.7)}
.sv-stat-2 .sv-stat-source{color:rgba(245,240,232,.65)}

/* CASE STUDY */
.sv-case{padding:clamp(72px,9vw,112px) var(--pad);background:var(--cream)}
.sv-case-inner{max-width:1100px}
.sv-case-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:clamp(28px,4vw,48px);align-items:start}
@media(max-width:700px){.sv-case-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
.sv-case-text p{font-size:clamp(13px,1.5vw,15px);line-height:1.9;color:rgba(26,26,26,.6);margin-bottom:18px}
.sv-case-text p:last-child{margin-bottom:0}
.sv-case-img{overflow:hidden;aspect-ratio:16/9}

/* RELATED INSIGHTS */
.sv-insights{padding:clamp(72px,9vw,112px) var(--pad);background:var(--cream);border-top:1px solid rgba(28,74,58,0.06)}
.sv-insights-inner{max-width:1100px}
.sv-insights-header{display:flex;align-items:flex-end;justify-content:space-between;flex-wrap:wrap;gap:16px;margin-bottom:clamp(32px,5vw,48px)}
.sv-insights-header .sv-h2{margin-bottom:0}
.sv-insights-all{font-size:12px;font-weight:600;color:var(--forest);border-bottom:1px solid rgba(28,74,58,0.3);padding-bottom:2px;text-decoration:none;transition:border-color .15s}
.sv-insights-all:hover{border-color:var(--forest)}
.sv-insights-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(3,1fr);gap:2px}
@media(max-width:700px){.sv-insights-grid{grid-template-columns:1fr}}
.sv-insight-card{background:var(--linen);padding:clamp(24px,3vw,34px);text-decoration:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;transition:background .2s}
.sv-insight-card:hover{background:#ddd8ce}
.sv-insight-tag{font-size:12px;font-weight:600;letter-spacing:.01em;color:var(--chartreuse-deep);margin-bottom:12px;display:block}
.sv-insight-title{font-family:'Bricolage Grotesque Variable',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(14px,1.8vw,18px);font-weight:700;line-height:1.25;color:var(--forest);margin-bottom:auto;padding-bottom:20px;flex:1}
.sv-insight-meta{display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;padding-top:14px;border-top:1px solid rgba(28,74,58,.1)}
.sv-insight-date{font-size:10px;color:rgba(28,74,58,.55)}
.sv-insight-arrow{font-size:11px;font-weight:600;color:var(--forest);opacity:.5;transition:opacity .2s}
.sv-insight-card:hover .sv-insight-arrow{opacity:1}

/* CTA */
.sv-cta{padding:clamp(72px,9vw,112px) var(--pad);background:var(--forest)}
.sv-cta-inner{max-width:660px}
.sv-cta-h2{font-family:'Bricolage Grotesque Variable',sans-serif;font-size:clamp(26px,4vw,52px);font-weight:800;letter-spacing:-0.04em;line-height:.97;color:var(--cream);margin-bottom:20px}
.sv-cta-sub{font-size:clamp(13px,1.5vw,16px);line-height:1.8;color:rgba(245,240,232,.45);margin-bottom:36px;display:block}
</style>
